Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @butter{4%tbsp} into ¼-inch cubes.

Trim and halve @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @marinara sauce{14%oz}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, ¾ cup water, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{} (you'll use the rest of the garlic powder and Italian seasoning in the next step).

Add marinara mixture to #oven-ready tray{1}; stir in @rigatoni pasta{6%oz} until thoroughly coated. Evenly top with half the butter cubes. Wash out bowl.

Toss mushrooms, zucchini, @shredded carrots{4%oz}, remaining garlic powder, remaining Italian seasoning, and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in bowl used for sauce. Season with salt and pepper.

Evenly top pasta mixture with veggies and remaining butter cubes.

Cover #foil{} tightly with foil; bake on top rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until pasta is al dente and veggies are tender, ~{60-65%minutes}. Let rest, covered, at least ~{5%minutes} before serving (be careful when uncovering—steam will release!).

While pasta bakes, pick @parsley{¼%oz}(leaves picked and torn) leaves from stems; tear leaves.

Divide pasta bake between shallow #bowls{}. Sprinkle with parsley and @parmesan cheese{6%tbsp}. Serve.

> This crowd-pleasing Italian-inspired baked pasta keeps prep and cleanup to a minimum, thanks to our convenient oven-ready tray.